On Escalation Ticket # 00422755 the new comment has been added: Marius-Viorel Iacob:

@WaitingOnEngineer 

	 - 	By it's nature hashing is used to "uniquely" identify files, as it's a fixed length "unique" digest of data stream. But we don't save hashes of files to flash drives. Are you referring to encryption used with EasyLock?
	 - 	EPP may uses various hashing algorithms for different purposes.
